reviews.review_text:
'85, He's Still [barely] Alive another Charlie Miller gem, this show is THE pinnacle of what early/mid-80s GD were all about. 

while the band was hitting stride with Brent having asserted himself JG was in some bad shape over the preceding summer and his vocals suffered badly for it (which is the lone downside in an otherwise phenomenal summer). 

Jerry apparently was feeling better come autumn and the two nights at the Fox Theater are proof. 
often overshadowed is the performance from the night before. 

highly recommended is the jam from Crazy Fingers into Drums; hell, the entire second set is a veritable showcase.

drums>space>wheel start from here

drums is great space is out there and spilled into the wheel
A plus Great sound; great show!

Hell in A Bucket Bobby Scream I've had this tape since 1985...my first show was the previous night. I've always loved Bobby's scream right after the bridge in Hell in a Bucket. After the last "Yeah, unable to dance I'll crawl" line you can hear him scream as he fades away from the mic. Classic Weir move.
Sailor-Saint Love this show--one of the first tapes I collected as a freshman in college back in '88.  My favorite version Sailor>Saint.
